    "created_at": "2015-09-07T20:04:43Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-07T20:04:43Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This goes through all 256 internal facings, which might be a nice checkbox-feature for voxels (though I doubt it would get used much even for them) but makes it quite slow and tiresome to rotate actors, even more so when they have only 16 or 8 visible facings.\n\nI'd prefer if you multiplied the delta with a value of 8, so that voxels and sprite actors with 32 facings change visible facing by 1/32 for every mousewheel 'step', actors with 16 facings 1 every 2 steps, actors with 8 facings 1 every 4 steps. An upper limit of 32 facings should be sufficient for both 1st-party and 3rd-party mods and would make rotation much faster and more responsive.\n\nMaybe you could expose the wheelstep multiplier to yaml so we can set it per mod and use 8 as default value, that would be even better.\n"
  },
